o\":\"keaising/im-select.nvim\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Switching and restoring input method automatically depends on Neovim's edit mode.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T18:57:09.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ripienaar/free-for-dev","categoryHTML":"<h2>Forms</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.formkeep.com/\">FormKeep.com</a> - Unlimited forms with 50 submissions per month, spam protection, email notification and a drag and drop designer that can export HTML. Additional features include custom field rules, teams and integrations to Google Sheets, Slack, ActiveCampaign and Zapier.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T17:33:14.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"rust-unofficial/awesome-rust","categoryHTML":"<h2>Development tools</h2><h3>Testing</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>Mutation Testing\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/sourcefrog/cargo-mutants\">cargo-mutants</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/sourcefrog/cargo-mutants\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">169</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":169,\"repo\":\"sourcefrog/cargo-mutants\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> [<a href=\"https://crates.io/crates/cargo-mutants\">cargo-mutants</a>] - Finds inadequately tested code by injecting mutations, no source changes required. <a href=\"https://github.com/sourcefrog/cargo-mutants/actions/workflows/tests.yml?query=branch%3Amain\"><img src=\"https://github.com/sourcefrog/cargo-mutants/actions/workflows/tests.yml/badge.svg?branch=main&#x26;event=push\" alt=\"build badge\"></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/llogiq/mutagen\">mutagen</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/llogiq/mutagen\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">517</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":517,\"repo\":\"llogiq/mutagen\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> [<a href=\"https://crates.io/crates/mutagen\">mutagen</a>] — A source-level mutation testing framework (nightly only) <a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/llogiq/mutagen\"><img src=\"https://api.travis-ci.org/llogiq/mutagen.svg?branch=master\" alt=\"build badge\"></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T16:41:46.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://residentmario.github.io/geoplot/\">Geoplot</a> - Geoplot is a high-level Python geospatial plotting library. It is an extension to cartopy and matplotlib which makes mapping easy: like seaborn for geospatial.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T16:24:24.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/giswqs/geemap\">Geemap</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/giswqs/geemap\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2.3k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":2322,\"repo\":\"giswqs/geemap\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A Python package for interactive mapping with Google Earth Engine, ipyleaflet, and ipywidgets.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T15:40:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/lgervasoni/urbansprawl\">Urbansprawl</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/lgervasoni/urbansprawl\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">56</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":56,\"repo\":\"lgervasoni/urbansprawl\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - The urbansprawl project provides an open source framework for assessing urban sprawl using open data. It uses OpenStreetMap (OSM) data to calculate its sprawling indices, divided in Accessibility, Land use mix, and Dispersion.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T15:40:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://xarray-spatial.org/\">Xarray-spatial</a> - Xarray-Spatial implements common raster analysis functions using Numba and provides an easy-to-install, easy-to-extend codebase for raster analysis.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T15:40:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://docs.momepy.org/en/stable/\">Momepy</a> - Momepy is a library for quantitative analysis of urban form - urban morphometrics. It is part of PySAL (Python Spatial Analysis Library) and is built on top of GeoPandas, other PySAL modules and networkX.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T15:40:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/global-healthy-liveable-cities/global-indicators\">global indicators</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/global-healthy-liveable-cities/global-indicators\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">31</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":31,\"repo\":\"global-healthy-liveable-cities/global-indicators\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Global healthy and sustainable city-indicators collaboration.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T15:40:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/rasterio/rasterio/blob/master/docs/index.rst\">rasterio</a> - Geographic information systems use GeoTIFF and other formats to organize and store gridded raster datasets such as satellite imagery and terrain models.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T15:40:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"unixorn/awesome-zsh-plugins","categoryHTML":"<h2>Themes</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/williamcanin/pyhack\">pyhack</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/williamcanin/pyhack\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1,\"repo\":\"williamcanin/pyhack\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Works well with dark terminal themes. Shows Python version, Python package version (pyproject.toml) and <code>git</code> current branch information.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T13:53:27.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CodyReichert/awesome-cl","categoryHTML":"<h2>Websockets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/3b/clws\">clws</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/3b/clws\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">72</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":72,\"repo\":\"3b/clws\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> -  websockets server in CL, built on IOlib and libfixposix. No licence specified.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T11:38:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CodyReichert/awesome-cl","categoryHTML":"<h2>Websockets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/joaotavora/hunchensocket\">Hunchensocket</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/joaotavora/hunchensocket\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">99</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":99,\"repo\":\"joaotavora/hunchensocket\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> -  RFC6455 compliant WebSockets for Common Lisp, as an extension to Hunchentoot. <a href=\"https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT\">MIT</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T11:38:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CodyReichert/awesome-cl","categoryHTML":"<h2>Websockets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/fukamachi/websocket-driver\">websocket-driver</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/fukamachi/websocket-driver\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">88</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":88,\"repo\":\"fukamachi/websocket-driver\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - based on Clack.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T11:38:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"TheComputerM/awesome-svelte","categoryHTML":"<h2>UI Components</h2><h3>Icons</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/aykutkardas/svelte-icomoon\">svelte-icomoon</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/aykutkardas/svelte-icomoon\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":3,\"repo\":\"aykutkardas/svelte-icomoon\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - It makes it very simple to use SVG icons in your Svelte projects.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T08:40:07.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ripienaar/free-for-dev","categoryHTML":"<h2>Security and PKI</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://wso2.com/asgardeo\">asgardeo.io</a> - Seamless Integration of SSO, MFA, passwordless auth and more. Includes SDKs for frontend and backend apps. Free up to 1000 MAUs and 5 identity providers.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T07:36:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/r-spatial/rgee\">Rgee</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/r-spatial/rgee\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">475</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":475,\"repo\":\"r-spatial/rgee\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Is an R binding package for calling Google Earth Engine API from within R. Various functions are implemented to simplify the connection with the R spatial ecosystem.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T04:43:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/sfnetworks/index.html\">Sfnetworks</a> - Provides a tidy approach to spatial network analysis.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T04:43:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/stars/index.html\">Stars</a> - Reading, manipulating, writing and plotting spatiotemporal arrays (raster and vector data cubes) in 'R'.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T04:43:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/stplanr/index.html\">stplanr</a> - Tools for transport planning with an emphasis on spatial transport data and non-motorized modes including OD data processing and other functions.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T04:43:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/motif/index.html\">Motif</a> - Describes spatial patterns of categorical raster data for any defined regular and irregular areas. It enables spatial analysis such as search, change detection, and clustering to be performed on spatial patterns.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T04:39:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/raster/index.html\">Raster</a> - Reading, writing, manipulating, analyzing and modeling of spatial data. The package implements basic and high-level functions for raster data and for vector data operations such as intersections.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T04:39:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/tmap/\">Tmap</a> - Thematic maps are geographical maps in which spatial data distributions are visualized. This package offers a flexible, layer-based, and easy to use approach to create thematic maps, such as choropleths and bubble maps.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T04:39:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"shuaibiyy/awesome-terraform","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.styra.com/terraform-cloud-config-management-with-styra-das-and-open-policy-agent\">Styra Declarative Authorization Service (DAS)</a> - Provides a managed <a href=\"https://www.openpolicyagent.org\">Open Policy Agent (OPA)</a> platform for Application and Infrastructure use cases, including Terraform, Terraform Cloud, and Kubernetes. Enforce policy guardrails during development, in CI/CD pipelines, and at deploy time. Styra DAS Free provides multiple systems and users, policy impact analysis, decision logging and replay, and access to Styra's Terraform policy library.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T03:36:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"springload/awesome-wagtail","categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Books</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.manning.com/books/wagtail-cms-in-action\">Wagtail CMS in Action</a> - Book about creating powerful, simple web applications using the Wagtail content management system.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-30T01:53:12.000Z"}]}},"pageContext":{"type":"day","from":1659139200000,"to":1659225599999,"previousId":"2022-07-31","nextId":"2022-07-29","nextName":"Jul 29th, 2022","previousName":"Jul 31st, 2022"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","2828988102"]}